### Legend
Sirrush, known in history as the Cloud Drake, the Bringer of Rain, or the Storm Dragon, lived for centuries among the highest mountains where clouds forever misted the peaks. He soared through the empty skies, a solitary monarch of the highlands. Over time, curious mortals began to settle the valleys and hillsides, bringing with them a wondrous gift: music. From the first hummed melodies to the delicate tunes of a maiden singing while she worked, Sirrush found himself captivated.

Dragons had song, in their own way. But this music from the fleeting lives of mortals was made more poignant by the fact that while generations passed, their music could live on. And so, this great dragon found himself entranced with gathering these songs.

Legends say that if you find yourself lost among the mountains and all hope seems gone, you must sing with all your heart. If your song is true, you may just gain the favor of the guardian of the mountains.

### Summoning Rules
- Spirit Level: 5th
- Alignment: Neutral Good (NG)
- Constellation: Dragon
- Binding DC: 23
#### Totems
You gain a +2 totem bonus on binding checks made with Sirrush if one of the following requirements is met, or a +4 bonus if all requirements are met:
- You perform a song from your homeland (requires 9 ranks in Perform (Singing)).
- You perform his ceremony atop a mountain peak or the highest rooftop in the settlement.
- You have a wind chime or other musical instrument that relies on air to produce sound.

#### Ceremony
You must burn heavy incense during the binding ritual to replicate the clouds of his home.
#### Manifestation
A wisp of steam begins to coil within the sigil, growing and twisting until a cloudy outline of a dragon's head appears. The rest of its body drifts in smoky ribbons. In a sing-song lilt, the deep voice hums a tune before asking, "sing me a song of your need..."
### Major Granted Abilities
- **Storm Breath (Su):** Sirrush was a dragon born of air and wind, and your breath weapon reflects that origin. You gain a breath weapon that unleashes a blast of hurricane-force winds in a 30-foot cone. Creatures caught in the cone take 1d6 bludgeoning damage per binder level (Reflex save for half). This breath also extinguishes all non-magical flames in the area. After using this ability, it becomes expended for 5 rounds.
- **Capstone Enhancement:** Creatures who fail the reflex save are also knocked prone on a failed Reflex save. This does not affect creatures who are one size or more larger than the binder.
### Minor Granted Abilities
- Song Smith: You gain Bardic Performance as a bard equal to  your binder level.You may use Bardic Performance for a number of rounds equal to 4 + your Charisma modifier per day, plus an additional round per 2 binder levels. The binder gains only the following types of bardic performance: countersong, fascinate, and inspire courage at 1st level; inspire greatness at 9th level (18th level Binder).
- I Will Guide The Way: While bound with Sirrush, the binder gains the Favored Terrain ability, but only for Mountains (and hills). When in his favored terrain, the binder grants all allies within line of sight and that can hear him a +2 bonus on initiative checks and Perception, Stealth, and Survival skill checks. Also, as long as they travel with him, the binders' allies leave no trail and cant be tracked. The binder can choose for the group to leave a trail, or even for specific members of the group to leave a trail if he so desires. (As the Terrain Bond (EX) ability of the ranger archetype, [Guide](https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/ranger/archetypes/paizo-ranger-archetypes/guide))
- Fly Above the Clouds (Su): You can transform into the essence of the Storm Dragonthe wind itself. As a standard action, you can assume a *gaseous form* (as the spell), gaining a fly speed of 60 feet with perfect maneuverability. In this form, you are immune to wind effects up to hurricane strength. You cannot attack with melee or natural weapons in this form, but may use spell-like or supernatural abilities that do not have a somatic or material component. You can use this ability for a number of rounds per day equal to 3 + your Charisma modifier, and these rounds need not be taken consecutively. 
- I Appreciate Your Song: You gain an insight bonus to Perform (Singing) and Diplomacy checks equal to half your binder level. In addition, you may take 10 on these skill checks even when distracted or threatened.
### Signs and Influence
*Sirrush, the Cloud Dragon affects you in the following ways*
- Physical Sign: Wisps of steam continuously float about your body, especially noticeable in cold or humid air.
- Personality Influence: Sirrush loved the settlements of mortals and the drama of their lives. He particularly adored performers and their talents. While bound to Sirrush, you feel compelled to join in if there is a bard or another singing performance nearby, raising your voice above the others to be heard.
- Favored Ally: Humanoid Performers
- Favored Enemies: Undead and Aberrations (who have no appreciation of music) 
### Vestigial Bond (Familiar)
You gain a pseudodragon familiar. Your binder level is treated as your wizard level when determining the familiar's abilities, hit points, and special abilities. This granted ability replaces Fly Above the Clouds.
